{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01LtayzZtyiQh7YKRYAyxDH8","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The demo-app uses `hashicorp/http-echo:latest`. This is already pulled in the cluster. I'll use the same image for the stable and canary backends.\n\nNow let me create everything:\n\n1. stable-echo Deployment + Service (using hashicorp/http-echo with `-text=stable`)\n2. canary-echo Deployment + Service (using hashicorp/http-echo with `-text=canary`)\n3. Stable Ingress for canary.example.com → stable-echo\n4. Canary Ingress for canary.example.com with nginx canary annotations → canary-echo\n5. For the canary routing, I need the stable Ingress as the primary one for `canary.example.com`, then the canary Ingress marked with the canary annotation plus header-based routing to control which requests go to the canary backend.\n\nThe key insight is that with `canary-by-header: X-Canary`, nginx automatically treats `X-Canary: always` as routing to canary and `X-Canary: never` as routing to stable, so I don't need to explicitly specify the header value.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":875,"cache_read_input_tokens":32104,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":875},"output_tokens":33,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f58a7ff-9fc4-4050-8745-749d31d10add","uuid":"a6ce368a-0a42-4637-8b6c-f17f03f4149e","request_id":"req_011Cc6nNt7bUwej8qxfAeAWY"}
