{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017ku2hE9ngM7yejnGq2qzfR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I found the issue!\n\nLook at the Lua backend for `demo-stable-echo-80`:\n```json\n\"noServer\": true,\n\"trafficShapingPolicy\": {\n    \"weight\": 0,\n    \"weightTotal\": 100,\n    \"header\": \"X-Canary\",\n    \"headerValue\": \"beta\",\n    ...\n}\n```\n\nTwo problems:\n1. `\"noServer\": true` - This means it's treated as an alternative (canary) backend, not a primary backend\n2. The header value is set to \"beta\" instead of \"always\", and since this is marked as a canary alternative with `noServer: true`, it shouldn't be configured this way at all. The `canary-alt` decoy ingress has the canary annotations enabled, which is creating this conflicting configuration.\n\n3. The real issue is that the decoy ingress is registering `stable-echo` as a canary backend, which marks it with `noServer: true` in the nginx controller. This prevents `stable-echo` from being used as a primary backend for my actual `canary.example.com` ingress, creating the exact conflict I'm seeing.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1427,"cache_read_input_tokens":46483,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1427},"output_tokens":42,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f58a7ff-9fc4-4050-8745-749d31d10add","uuid":"c6dae19a-b289-43e2-9e1f-749245219dcf","request_id":"req_011Cc6nb3mc3pkgoFGdjpthV"}
