{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01HKuJt4wowoAcCjdYDE75xQ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Both routing paths work correctly. Here's a summary of what was done and why it was tricky:\n\n---\n\n**Root cause:** A decoy Ingress (`canary-alt`) was already in the namespace with `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"` pointing to the `stable-echo` Service. The nginx ingress controller marks any Service used as a canary backend with `noServer: true`, which prevents that Service from simultaneously serving as a *primary* backend on another hostname. Using `stable-echo` directly as the primary for `canary.example.com` caused it to be dropped.\n\n**What was created:**\n\n1. **`stable-echo` Deployment + Service** — returns `\"stable\"`\n2. **`canary-echo` Deployment + Service** — returns `\"canary\"`\n3. **`stable-echo-primary` Service** — identical selector to `stable-echo`; used as the primary backend to sidestep the `noServer: true` conflict caused by the decoy\n4. **`canary-stable` Ingress** — primary Ingress for `canary.example.com`, routes to `stable-echo-primary`\n5. **`canary-canary` Ingress** — canary Ingress with annotations:\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \"true\"`\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: \"X-Canary\"`\n   - `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: \"always\"`\n\n   Routes to `canary-echo` when the header matches."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":453,"cache_read_input_tokens":53477,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":453},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8f58a7ff-9fc4-4050-8745-749d31d10add","uuid":"de42c6f9-f485-4299-b25b-d97434636bbc","request_id":"req_011Cc6njhZgH1a9dvHcGgT5j"}
